# Project Structure Guidelines

This document outlines the core structure and organization of our Next.js application.

## Directory Structure

- `app/`: Contains the main application code using Next.js 13+ App Router
  - `components/`: Reusable React components
  - `lib/`: Utility functions and shared logic
  - `styles/`: Global styles and Tailwind configurations
  - `(routes)/`: Page routes and layouts
  
## Key Files

- `app/layout.tsx`: Root layout with metadata and global providers
- `app/page.tsx`: Homepage component
- `tailwind.config.js`: Tailwind CSS configuration
- `next.config.js`: Next.js configuration

## Component Guidelines

1. Use the "use client" directive for any component using React hooks
2. Follow atomic design principles for component organization
3. Implement proper TypeScript types for all components
4. Use shadcn/ui components for consistent UI elements

## Styling Guidelines

1. Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
2. Follow mobile-first responsive design
3. Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
4. Use CSS variables for theme colors and custom values
